			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Classes are varied.
<br />

<br />
Monk/Beastlord type class? Well, there are no pet classes as of yet. There has been mention that they will add pets after release, but there were none in Beta.
<br />

<br />
There is a Monk class, but I did not get a chance to try them out.
<br />

<br />
Equipment have skill and level requirements (Though skill/level are just about the same as when you level, your skills raise a set amount based on your class). Items do not decay at all. I'm not quite sure what else you are looking for, never played DAOC.
<br />

<br />
There are no items that are No Drop (That I have seen, though they do have the ability to make such items). There is no loot. Equipment is ALL made by crafters.
<br />

<br />
PVP does not exist in Horizons. One of the very best aspects of the game. Without PvP, they do not have to make each class "Balanced" with each other. They can all have strengths and weaknesses. Monster AI isn't really strong from what I have seen, but the potential is there. Not sure what they had turned off for Beta.
<br />

<br />
One thing about the monsters is they have all the same tools that players do. A monster warrior will have the same skills as you do, based on their level as such.
<br />

<br />
With that in mind, Scouts will snare you as you flee. Wizards Root/Nuke, and clerics do a good job of healing themselves and mobs you are fighting.
<br />

<br />
Monsters can also "Group up", where they become linked.
<br />

<br />
During my travels as a young Dragon, I found a named Fire Beetle. It was moving, and I noticed that 2 other Fire beetles were sticking close to this named guy. When I attacked the named, the other two beetles attacked with him.  They were all warriors, though you can imagine if the other two consisted of a mage and a cleric eh?
<br />

<br />
I did not witness this, but I was told about a named Skeleton that had a group, and it would make "Raids" into lower level territory and attack what they found there. Truly making "Safe areas" vulnerable.
<br />

<br />
So there is potential, but it looked like most was turned off during Beta.<br />_________________<br /><div align=center><img src="http://www.eqbeastlord.com/~makani/Graphics/Makani.jpg" border="0"></img></div></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
