				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Whats the maximum player group size?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Groups can handle 8 people.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">How well can most classes solo?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Every class can solo to varrying degrees.
<br />

<br />
Without PvP there is no need for total class balancing. Some classes have strengths and weaknesses. For Example: Spiritists use a form of ethereal attack, which is hard to defend against. Thus they can end up doing a lot of damage in the right situations. Far more than any other class. However, against something with a defense to ethereal (Ghosts might end up resistant to said damage) they will not do as well. Same for weapon types.
<br />

<br />
There is a reason to have a Sword and a Maul. Blunt damage and Slash damage have different resistances. Like old D&D where a skeleton takes more damage from blunt vs. piercing...
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">How's the UI?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The UI is pretty customizable, so far you can't add your own graphics like EQ's UI, but you can move every window, there are a lot of filter options, transpancy and window labels are all customizable as well as autohiding windows that move to the side of the screen unless you hovor your mouse over them. There is much room for improvement such as being able to change chatbox labels to create "Battle", "Chat", and "Tells". Currently, they all say "Chat" or "Chat:(Insert Filter Here)"
<br />

<br />
All in all, I really like it. Would like even more if we could add our own graphical images for windows.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Is combat intensive or click and watch?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Combat is what you make of it. You are quite able to click and watch, and you can play an active roll. There are LOTS of special skills you gain as you level. As a lvl 15 Dragon Warrior 15 Cleric, I had 3 seperate hotkey bars of skills/spells. (Though they recently changed Dragons entirely.) 
<br />

<br />
One of the downfalls currently is Stances. Origionally they were Offensive and Defensive in nature. If you were in one stance, you did more damage but got hit more often. Currently it's a game of Rock Paper Scissors with a little extra. If you are in Rock stance you do more damage against someone in Scissor stance, but take more from Paper stance.
<br />

<br />
However some skills are linked to what stance you are in, so if you are in rock stance you cannot use Uber slash of doom. So you have to decide if Uber slash of doom is worth taking extra damage for a while, or if you want to wait for your opponent to make a switch that allows you freedom to move to that stance. Other skills are useable in any stance, but gain power in certain stances.
<br />

<br />
It's not extremely well done, but there is distinct potential.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">How are quests done?  Camp for those rare drops or is it all about having the quest?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
There is no camping at all. (Well, not entirely true, some quests ask you to go kill Bob the Tyrant). The quest system is pretty robust, but they held back a lot of content. The basic quests were fedex delieveries and Kill XXX level XXX monsters type. They have far more available, but they didn't want to spoil a bunch of quests so we got generic ones. The system allows for stages of the quest to complete.
<br />

<br />
For example, a quest can tell you to go kill 20 zombies, and bring back 10 fingers. Each section will update as you complete it. This allows for a quest such as this. "Go forth and locate the 3 books of knowledge, you must also prove you scaled Mt Death, and you must also gain knighthood in the brotherhood of shame."
<br />

<br />
You can do the quest in any order and with no time limit. It will check off the parts you finish, and you will know where you stand via the quest log.
<br />

<br />
You might find 1 book, then go scale Mt Death to get flagged as having done so. Then finish the rest to finally finish the quest.<br />_________________<br /><div align=center><img src="http://www.eqbeastlord.com/~makani/Graphics/Makani.jpg" border="0"></img></div></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
