			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Never played Shadowbane. PvP is crap.
<br />

<br />
Hard to describe all the classes as I didn't get to test them all. Dragons were changed at the very end to in themselves be a class. Sorta like D&D where Elf was a class like Rogue. The end dragon was a Warrior with some really interesting abilities. They also seemed to be AOE focused. They added a few AE abilities/spells in the last patch, and upgraded breath weapon when you age is supposed to be AE. Will be interesting to see how viable that ends up being.
<br />

<br />
Warriors are what you would expect. They have melee power. They also have a few defensive abilities and abilities that draw attacks to themselves.
<br />

<br />
Clerics are also a bit like warriors with healing powers and buffs. A lot of cleric abilites also focus on taking the punishment from others. They obtain a skill that protects another player from spells and redirects them to the Cleric, same with melee damage. They have quite nice damage so are more like a D&D version cleric.
<br />

<br />
Healers are much more focused on healing (Duh), at the sacrifice of the melee abilities.
<br />

<br />
Mages are exactly what you would expect. Damage dealers, but they sure soak up the hits like a sponge.
<br />

<br />
One of the really interesting Bi-ped classes is the Chaos warrior. A lot of their abilities are "Flip a coin, if it's heads you get a powerup, if it's tails you get kicked in the nuggets."
<br />

<br />
There are a lot of other classes that I had no experience with such as Crossbowmen, Spearmen, Rangers, Scouts, Reavers, Paladins, Wizards, Guardians, Knights of Creation, Elemental Archers, Monks and such. There are simply a ton of classes in the game.<br />_________________<br /><div align=center><img src="http://www.eqbeastlord.com/~makani/Graphics/Makani.jpg" border="0"></img></div></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
