				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Crimsontalon wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">How cutomizable are the dragons really?   (a true fashion whore here)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Well, there is always room for improvement, but there are quite a few options.
<br />

<br />
There are 6 head styles which are slightly modifiable by 13 scale textures, There are 17 "Decals" (Racing Stripes, Dots, Tattoo swirlies), about 9 Chest scale styles, 4 Different Eye shapes, and about 17 Scale Colors, 9 Chest scale colors, 6 Decal colors, Highlights, and you can adjust your muscularity, height, and portliness.
<br />

<br />
You can make a pink dragon with purple polkadots unfortunatly.
<br />

<br />
I was hoping that decals could be white, I wanted a green dragon with white spots....didn't work out. Decal colors are a bit limited, but that would be easy to change and add more options.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I admit dragons are the very reason i became intersted in this game.
