Actually, Adulthood's real life timer has been set at 60 Days. No word on Ancient, but it is speculated as much longer.
<br />

<br />
However, there are other requirements. Hoard size, Skill levels (Both by levelling and quests), and a special ceremony quest.
<br />

<br />
During beta there was PLENTY of people that did not play Dragons. I would have to say that there were quite a lot of Dragons though. But a LOT of them didn't like the changes to the way a Dragon played.
<br />

<br />
If you want good reviews, check out Tazoon.com IGN has always been a cesspool, the fact that they are the "Official" forums is quite sad....
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The thing is... EVERYONE is probably going to play a dragon, at least for a while. They are going to have to make dragons less effective than most other classes to balance the whole "cool factor", or else it's going to be a dragon-dominated game.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That's what I thought too. However, there are a LOT of things Dragons don't have. Useable equipment. We have scale slots, a scale backpack, and a Cargo disk slot. That's it. 
<br />

<br />
So if you want to have a "Cool looking set of armor and a wicked sword of doom with neato flames!" Yer out of luck =) Once you make your dragon, the only change in appearance is when you age...
<br />

<br />
Being stuck to a single Class is also something. There are no prestige classes for Dragons, the only way to be different is to complete different ability quests and such.
<br />

<br />
Crafting takes a hit as well. The only "Items" you can make are only useable by dragons except for spells. Those are useable by players. I didn't experience this, but you also cannot contribute as much to player built structures. As far as I know, all we can contribute is raw materials, like being a Dumptruck carrying bricks to a building and giving it to the construction workers.
<br />

<br />
Also, the hoard plays a large part in your effectiveness as a dragon. The hoard size determines the strength of your Breath Weapon and your scales armor factor. So anything you DO get, you are tempted to toss right into your hoard (Blackhole)
<br />

<br />
Dragons are definatly not for everyone. Though I am sure it will be flooded, it will end up being like the "Flavor of the Month" in EQ, tons of them, but not so many at high levels.
<br />

<br />
