				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Silverak wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Not trying to douse Horizons at all Makani but of all the boards I read, you're the only one that's very gung ho on it.  Alot of people say. "it's good BUT.. blah blah blah."  Seems like a game that will need some balancing and content added to be a real contender in the MMORPG market.  I don't have the time of money to switch to any other game at the moment other than EQ or Halo, but I just wanted to say that.  No personal opinion as I decided not join beta.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I'm not here to persuade you to buy the game. I just wanted to let people ask questions about my experiences in Horizons. Including what is wrong with the game. I have no problem saying that there were plenty of bugs, and that some really nasty ones were released. (UK already is playing)
<br />

<br />
However a lot of the negative reviews you are reading are by people that stopped playing Beta for the last 2 months because "It was too buggy to log in!" then posting crap like "NPC's don't even load!"......well, yeah.....5 beta patches ago. That's one of the major bugs that they DID fix. Or my favorite. They have a TON of memory leaks! At one point they had identified over 10,000 memory leaks. Near the end of beta they fixed all but 9 or them.
<br />

<br />
Negative reviews are always far worse than the truth is. I'm just giving an honest response to the questions asked of me. I'm not here to tell people to go and buy the game. I'm here to answer questions people might have had that were interested and just...forgot about it. Which a lot of people did because of the whole Blackout-Hostile Takeover thing.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Kivahri Raynsmajic wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">hehem kewl.... i make practically all the recommended specs except for the ram, lol
