<br />

<br />
Ram is pretty essential, at least it's cheap to upgrade.
<br />

<br />
Learning curve? The game is pretty darn easy to learn. Almost too easy. In fact, way too easy. That's one of the things I think they needed to change. When you level you should have been given points to spend in your skills. That way a warrior that wanted to be a good damage taker would spend his points on armor while another that wanted damage would increase his weapon skills.
<br />

<br />
Combat can be done by hitting attack and walking out of the room if you really want to. There are a lot of skills you get for combat if you are an adventurer, so you can actually make combat interesting. There is definatly room for improvement here.
<br />

<br />
Crafting is pretty easy as well and quite robust and with more in the works that didn't make release.
<br />

<br />
To make everything even easier. The tutorial is really quick, and easy, and gives you most of what you need to know.[/quote]<br />_________________<br /><div align=center><img src="http://www.eqbeastlord.com/~makani/Graphics/Makani.jpg" border="0"></img></div></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
